                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d900">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 850a.001M33.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose, with office copy, a letter<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d900fn1">Not printed.</note> addressed by the President to Her Royal
                    Highness, Marie Adelaide, acknowledging the letter of June 18 last, by which Her
                    Royal Highness announced that, having attained her majority, she had taken
                    possession of the Sovereign Power of the Grand Duchy of Luxemburg.</p>
                <p>You will forward the copy to the Foreign Office of Luxemburg and deliver the
                    original in the manner most agreeable to Her Royal Highness.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
